'''''Children Underground''''' is a [[2001]] [[documentary film]] directed by [[Edet Belzberg]]. It follows a group of abandoned adolescent [[street children]] who live in the [[Romania]]n subway system. The street kids are encountered daily with commuter adults passing them by in the station as they starve, swindle, and steal, all while searching desparately for a fresh can of spray paint to get high with.

The documentary was shot in two separate time periods.

The film has won the Special Jury Prize at the [[2001]] [[Sundance Film Festival]]. It was nominated for the [[Academy Award for Documentary Feature|Academy Award for Best documentary feature]].

